<body>

    <div id="content">
    <h1>Automated testing of ticketing application</h1>

    <h2>Please enter ticketing system data. All fields required.<br>The results will show the probability of not recording zone 2 by changing accuracy between 20% and 100%.</h2>
    <br>

    <h2>Zones<br>Choose the size of the fare-zones. Zone 2 is the critical zone you want to analyse.</h2>

    <div id="zones">
    <h2>Zone 1</h2>
    <select name="zone1" id="zone1">
        <option value="s">small</option>
        <option value="m">medium</option>
        <option value="l">large</option>
    </select>

    <h2>Zone 2</h2>
    <select name="zone2" id="zone2">
        <option value="s">small</option>
        <option value="m">medium</option>
        <option value="l">large</option>
    </select>

    <h2>Zone 3</h2>
    <select name="zone3" id="zone3">
        <option value="s">small</option>
        <option value="m">medium</option>
        <option value="l">large</option>
    </select>
    </div>

    <h2>Variables<br>Enter values for variables. (As percentage, e.g. 10 for 10%)</h2>

    <div id="variables">
    <h2>Proability of phone failure<br>Suggestion: 0.1</h2>
    <input name="phone_failure" type="text" id="phone_failure" placeholder="0.1"/>

    <h2>Probability user forgets check-in<br>Suggestion: 0.1</h2>
    <input name="ci_failure" type="text" placeholder="0.1" id="ci_failure"/>

    <h2>Proability of getting no location using GSM<br>Suggestion: 10</h2>
    <input name="gsm_failure" type="text" placeholder="10" id="gsm_failure"/>

    <h2>Probability of getting no location using Wi-Fi<br>Suggestion: 10</h2>
    <input name="wifi_failure" type="text" placeholder="10" id="wifi_failure"/>

    <h2>Probability of getting no location using GPS<br>Suggestion: 33</h2>
    <input name="gps_failure" type="text" placeholder="33" id="gps_failure"/>
    <br>
    </div>

    <div id="buttons">
    <input type="button" class="btn" value="Run PRISM Script" onclick="RunFile();"/>
    <input type="button" class="btn" value="Show Results" onclick="openResult();"/>
    </div>

    <div id="buttons">
    <input type="button" class="btn" value="close" onClick="self.close();"> 
    </div>

    </div>
</body>
</html>